content:
Customize Additional Chat Branding

Set the base font size, width and height, and images for your Embedded Chat deployment.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Embedded Service setup node is available in: Lightning Experience
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To set up Embedded Chat:	Customize Application AND Modify Metadata

The legacy chat product is scheduled for retirement on February 14, 2026. Migrate to Messaging for In-App and Web before that date.

From Setup, enter Embedded Service in the Quick Find box, then select Embedded Service.
Select the Embedded Service deployment that you want to work with by clicking the arrow beside the deployment name and selecting View.
Click Edit next to Chat Settings.
In the Additional branding section, click Edit.
In the Images & Dimensions tab, set your chat images:
Agent Avatar (40 px by 40 px)
Logo (36 px by 36 px)
Pre-Chat Background (320 px by 100 px)
Waiting State (250 px by 60 px)
Set the width and height of your chat window. Set the base font size for your chat window.
Click Finish to close the window.

Customize Embedded Chat Labels
Create your own custom labels and manage the label language for your Embedded Chat deployment.
The primary language for a chat window is set in your embedded code snippet. An extra step in Translation Workbench is required for custom labels or platform-only languages.
title: Customizing Embedded Chat Branding
